      "description": "Up for sale is a 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant with VarioCam Plus technology. This high-revving unit is mated to a G96 six-speed manual transaxle, providing an engaging, analog driving experience. The vehicle is mechanically sorted, featuring an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh Rear Main Seal (RMS). Performance is enhanced by a set of Bilstein B8 dampers and M030-spec sway bars, sharpening turn-in and minimizing body roll. While the exterior reflects its history as a true driver's car, the drivetrain remains robust with excellent compression across all cylinders. This is a technically sound example for the enthusiast prioritizing chassis dynamics and mechanical integrity over concours-level aesthetics.",
